# GitHub Pages routing

Production is deployed to a project site with base path `/golden-ladle` (`GITHUB_PAGES=true` in CI). Local dev uses an empty base.

- Import `base` from `$app/paths` for `<a href>` attributes: `href="{base}/leagues"`.
- Use `` goto(`${base}/path`) `` for programmatic navigation — bare `goto('/')` resolves to the domain root and 404s on GitHub Pages.
- For auth/route guards, use `$page.route.id` (e.g. `/login`), not `$page.url.pathname` (e.g. `/golden-ladle/login`).
- `svelte.config.js` sets `paths.base`; do not hardcode `/golden-ladle` in source — always use `{base}`.

## Examples

```svelte
<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<a href="{base}/login">Sign in</a>
goto(`${base}/leagues`);

<!-- ❌ BAD on GitHub Pages -->
<a href="/login">Sign in</a>
goto('/');
publicRoutes.has($page.url.pathname);
```
